### In popular culture

Wax figures of Reagan, Thatcher, and Gorbachev at [Madame Tussauds](/Madame_Tussauds), London.

In 2020 and 2021, the [Theatre of Nations](/Theatre_of_Nations) in Moscow, in collaboration with Latvian director [Alvis Hermanis](/Alvis_Hermanis), staged a production titled *Gorbachev*. [Yevgeny Mironov](/Yevgeny_Mironov_(actor)) and [Chulpan Khamatova](/Chulpan_Khamatova) portrayed Gorbachev and his wife Raisa, respectively.

Gorbachev has been depicted by [David Dencik](/David_Dencik) in the 2019 miniseries [Chernobyl](/Chernobyl_(miniseries)), by [Matthew Marsh](/Matthew_Marsh_(actor)) in the 2023 film [Tetris](/Tetris_(film)), and by [Aleksander Krupa](/Aleksander_Krupa) in the 2024 biographical drama *Reagan*.

Gorbachev makes an appearance in the video game [Call of Duty: Black Ops Cold War](/Call_of_Duty:_Black_Ops_Cold_War) during a mission where the player infiltrates the [KGB headquarters](/Lubyanka_Building). Gorbachev is portrayed by David Agranov.

